# Kanban

## Kanban Entry List

This endpoint displays the Kanban board.

> The API returns JSON structured like this for the user part:

```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "profile_image": "https://example.com/media/image.png",
      "username": "LokeHagberg",
      "group": 1,
      "created_by": 1, 
      "assignee": 1,
      "title": "tasktitle", 
      "description": "taskdescription", 
      "tag": 1
    }, ...
  ]
}
```

> The API returns JSON structured like this for the group part:

```json
{
  "data": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "LokeHagbergGroup"
      "image": "https://example.com/media/image.png",
      "group": 1,
      "created_by": 1, 
      "assignee": 1,
      "title": "tasktitle", 
      "description": "taskdescription", 
      "tag": 1
    }, ...
  ]
}
```

### HTTP Request

`GET <%= config[:endpoint] %>/group/<group_id>/kanban/`

### Query Parameters 

| Parameter                                 | Notes                                                               |
|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `group_id` *int, optional*                |                                                                     |
| `created_by` *int, optional*              |                                                                     |
| `assignee` *int, optional*                |                                                                     |
| `title__icontains` *str, optional*        |                                                                     |
| `description__icontains` *str, optional*  |                                                                     |
| `tag` *int, optional*                     | An integer between 1 and 5 for the five columns in the Kanban board |


## Kanban Entry Create

This endpoint creates an entry in a Kanban board.

> The API returns JSON structured like this:

```json
{
  "data": 1
}
```

### HTTP Request

`POST <%= config[:endpoint] %>/group/<group_id>/kanban/create`

### Body Parameters 

| Parameter                     | Notes |
|-------------------------------|-------|
| `assignee` *str, optional*    |       |
| `assignee` *int, optional*    |       |
| `title` *str, optional*       |       |
| `description` *str, optional* |       |
| `tag` *int, optional*         |       |


